widgets_values:
a female knight with long, flowing red hair, wearing ornate silver and gold armor with a purple cape.
a female elf warrior with long white hair and pointed ears, wearing a green and silver armor set with intricate designs.
The female knight and the female elf are talking to the viewer.
Background is a stunning landscape photograph featuring a lone red tree standing in the middle of a lush green meadow filled with vibrant pink flowers, set against a backdrop of snow-capped mountains under a clear blue sky with fluffy white clouds.

All ref images have to be the same resolution.
Though image list can maintain resolution for each ref image but ComfyUI will run multiple times.

VACE reference image can be the same as the common ref image generated based on the video first frame. However, it can be more complicated using 1 to 3 reference images, including main subjects with a white background and/or background image, batch/concatenate them as one image grid with/without scaling them to the project/video resolution.

1. Build your reference images yourself using 1-3 images based on the need.
2. Link the chosen one (brown color) to the Setter.
Use padding and target (height) resolution to control the size of the subject relative to the image. In theory, the bigger the subject relative to the image, the better the result.
a group node cannot link to set node directly. So that link the Image Input Switch JK🐉 node - image_false slot instead.

widgets_values:
Wan Video Torch Compile Settings will not take effect if you're using fp8 diffusion model and your graphic card is 20xx or 30xx.

If you choose VACE fp32/bf16/fp16 model, then you can:

nodes.title: Triton
widgets_values:
Wan Video Torch Compile Settings will not take effect if you're using fp8 diffusion model and your graphic card is 20xx or 30xx.

If you choose VACE fp32/bf16/fp16 model, then you can:
1. Link Wan Video Torch Compile Settings to the Wan Video Model Loader to speed up about 15%~25%..
2. Follow the VRAM settings instruction in the Wan Video Wrapper Tips Group.

For single reference image only:
1. The reference image should be as close as possible to the first frame of the control video. 
2. Bypass crop by mask and resize node in the Load Reference Group.
3. Enable this group and link to the WanVideo VACE Encode node's ref_image slot to replace the first 3 frames of control video with the reference image.
